&lt;br /&gt;
i have a number of same backups like &quot;mydatabase1234.bak&quot;&lt;br /&gt;
&quot;mydatabase1235.bak&quot; and so on. i want to restore the latest one,ie mydatabase1235.bak.how should i do that. here my bak file is not that static as you have mentioned above..&lt;br /&gt;
please help me out

I do the following for about 6 or 7 databases that I backup and restore between 2 servers every night. These are small databases (less than 40 GB). I also just do a full backup and don&#039;t need differential, I do like all the options you have in your SSIS package, I have to check it out&lt;br /&gt;
&lt;br /&gt;
&lt;br /&gt;
&lt;br /&gt;
it is a  3 step SQLAgent job&lt;br /&gt;
&lt;br /&gt;
&lt;br /&gt;
&lt;br /&gt;
--Step 1, this will backup the DB to the server I want it restored to&lt;br /&gt;
&lt;pre&gt;exec OrigServer.MyDataBase.dbo.prBackupMyDataBase&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;br /&gt;
&lt;br /&gt;
--step 2 restore DB and fix permissions&lt;br /&gt;
&lt;pre&gt;USE master&lt;br /&gt;
GO&lt;br /&gt;
ALTER DATABASE MyDataBase SET SINGLE_USER WITH ROLLBACK IMMEDIATE&lt;br /&gt;
GO&lt;br /&gt;
RESTORE DATABASE MyDataBase FROM  DISK = N&#039;D:MyDataBase.BAK&#039; WITH  FILE = 1,  &lt;br /&gt;
NOUNLOAD,  REPLACE,  STATS = 1&lt;br /&gt;
GO&lt;br /&gt;
ALTER DATABASE MyDataBase SET MULTI_USER&lt;br /&gt;
GO&lt;br /&gt;
Use MyDataBase&lt;br /&gt;
GO&lt;br /&gt;
EXECUTE sp_change_users_login &#039;Update_One&#039;, &#039;SomeName&#039;, &#039;SomeName&#039;&lt;br /&gt;
&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;br /&gt;
&lt;br /&gt;
--Step 3 is a Operating System command&lt;br /&gt;
&lt;br /&gt;
del d:MyDataBase.BAK&lt;br /&gt;
&lt;br /&gt;
And that is it
